name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: Pic: after the race Jack Brabham was exhausted but satisfied, having won his first #F1 world championship. So, all in all, Sebring ’59 wasn’t a bad season-ending & world championship-deciding F1 GP, was it? Let’s hope today measures up. (5/5)  https://t.co/ArJsM2EGbz

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: Tony Brooks had driven a superb race, carving his way from the back to finish a brilliant 3rd. But the winner was 22-year-old Bruce McLaren (pic: chasing his Cooper team leader Brabham), becoming the then-youngest #F1 GP winner of all time, a record that lasted 43 years. (4/5)  https://t.co/52jqRv1QLd

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: So Jack Brabham took the lead & looked to be sitting pretty for the world championship. However, on the last lap he ran out fuel, so he got out & pushed his Cooper 400 metres uphill to the finish line, ending up 4th, & duly taking a very hard-earned title. (3/5)  https://t.co/5QZDKVCVJD

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: 3 drivers were in contention for the #F1 world championship: Jack Brabham, Stirling Moss, Tony Brooks. Moss led from pole, but DNF’d on lap 6 (gearbox). Brooks (pic) was rammed by his team-mate & lost a lot of time in the pits while his Ferrari was being checked for damage. (2/5)  https://t.co/vKHGGbWtRb

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈

tweet: Remembering Dave Charlton, born #OnThisDay in ’36, rapid South African who started 11 #F1 GPs for Brabham, Lotus & (privateer) McLaren (’65-75) but won the #SouthAfricanChampionship 6 times on the trot (’70-75). Pic: drifting his McLaren M23 at Kyalami in ’75, his last GP. (1/2)  https://t.co/8LKCMpubDC

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: Remembering Milanese gentleman racer Luigi Piotti, born #OnThisDay in 1913. He started 5 ’50s GPs in Maseratis, but was too slow for #F1. Pic: Piotti’s 250F (car #28) in the pits with Fangio’s (#2), Argentina ’57; Piotti finished 10th, 10 laps behind the winner, Fangio.  https://t.co/Ae2wT4lYCz

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: #OnThisDay in 2013 took place the 3rd & last #IndianGP, won by Seb Vettel, now of @AstonMartinF1, who had also won the previous 2 Indian GPs. Pic: afterwards he performed donuts & cavorted beside his car to celebrate his 4th consecutive championship & was thus fined €25,000.  https://t.co/WV1GjUyyo4

name: Matt Bishop 🏳️‍🌈
tweet: #OnThisDay in ’63, in Mexico, Clark (Lotus), who’d bagged pole by 1.7sec, led from start to finish, drove fastest lap - the 4th of his record 8 #F1 grands chelems - & beat the rest by 101sec. Yes, that’s 1min 41sec. Pic: wheelspinning away from Surtees’ Ferrari on the startline.  https://t.co/ndoexW983V
